This research-oriented project aims to develop a robust framework for Authorship Verificationâ€”determining whether a specific author wrote a given text. Unlike standard attribution, this framework is designed to operate in adversarial environments, effectively handling short texts, domain shifts, and intentional writing style imitation.
The solution integrates:
â€¢	Contextual Embeddings: Using BERT to capture semantic meaning.
â€¢	Hybrid Neural Architecture: A CNN-BiLSTM layer for stylistic pattern extraction and sequential flow modeling.
â€¢	Adversarial Training: Implementing the Impostor Projection Method to improve resilience against forgery.
â€¢	Signal Analysis: Treating text as a temporal signal and using Dynamic Time Warping (DTW) for alignment.
Anomaly Detection: Utilizing Isolation Forest to flag suspicious texts.
